15
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:36,000
{\an2}{\pos(210.5,244.05)}第三季  第二集

16
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:46,950
正好你提到任人唯亲  参议员
I'm glad you brought up nepotism, Senator.

17
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,330
如果总统是直接任命
Um, if this were an outright appointment,

18
00:01:49,330 --> 00:01:50,310
情况肯定不同
that would be one thing,

19
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:53,190
但他只能提名我而已
but in this case, the president can only nominate.

20
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:56,120
我的能力得由参议院认可
It's the Senate that deems me worthy.

21
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,580
我正是来博得你们的认可的
I'm here to convince you that I am.

22
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:00,040
不过说实话
Although, I must admit,

23
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:02,150
我丈夫上完厕所从不放下马桶圈
my husband never remembers to put the toilet seat down,

24
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:04,600
他也可能是想补偿我
so he could be trying to make it up to me.

25
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:08,990
我更担心的是你缺乏经验
My larger concern is your experience. You have very little.

26
00:02:08,990 --> 00:02:12,300
十年前  我成立了个小慈善组织
Well, a decade ago, I founded a small nonprofit

27
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:15,230
后来影响力逐渐遍及全球
and I built it into a major global player.

28
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:19,180
我代表我的组织在国会通过了数项法案
I shepherded a number of bills through Congress on its behalf.

29
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:19,960
而去年一年
And over the last year,

30
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:23,020
我都致力于性侵法案改革
I've dedicated myself to sexual assault reform,

31
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:25,140
已经取得可喜进展
and have made meaningful strides.

32
00:02:25,510 --> 00:02:28,320
虽然算不上治国才能
Now, while this may not qualify as statecraft,

33
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:30,180
但也表明了我的能力
it does illustrate my effectiveness,

34
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:33,950
我也希望在联合国发挥我的能力
the same effectiveness I plan on bringing to the United Nations.

35
00:02:33,950 --> 00:02:37,290
谢谢  安德伍德夫人  我放弃我剩余的时间
Thank you, Mrs. Underwood. I yield the remainder of my time.

36
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:42,550
北达科塔州的华莱士夫人  您有八分钟
Uh, Mrs. Wallace of North Dakota, you have eight minutes.

37
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:44,240
谢谢  主席先生
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

38
00:02:44,550 --> 00:02:47,660
安德伍德夫人  我细问一下
Mrs. Underwood, allow me to get specific.

39
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:51,110
您对联合国9214号决议
What is your take on UN Resolution 9214,

40
00:02:51,110 --> 00:02:54,310
强行赦免刚果境内
the imposition of sanctions on the Congo for the--

41
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:57,390
非法采煤以及走私煤矿行为的看法吗
The illegal mining and smuggling of mineral resources.

42
00:02:57,390 --> 00:03:00,960
是的  美国投了反对票
Yes. The United States voted against this resolution.

43
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:04,480
刚果共和国经济本就欠发达
The DRC is already wracked with economic hardship,

44
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:06,420
再加上政治局势不稳定
compounded by an unstable government.

45
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:10,490
煤矿几乎是唯一的人均GDP来源
It ranks 192 out of 194 in GDP per capita.

46
00:03:10,870 --> 00:03:12,920
我认为我们应该鼓励外国资本进入
I think we need to encourage foreign investment

47
00:03:12,930 --> 00:03:15,450
发展新的经济增长模式
and develop new forms of economic growth

48
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:18,670
而不是让刚果一穷到底
rather than make one of the world's poorest countries even poorer.

49
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:20,400
从国家安全角度考虑
From a national security perspective,

50
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,620
刚果的繁荣发展
the United States maintains

51
00:03:21,620 --> 00:03:24,720
仍对美国是有利的
a strong interest in the success of the DRC.

52
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,880
-我们需要刚果稳定...  -他们来了
- We want a stable nation... - They're here.

53
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,710
...才能助我国对抗
...that can help us in combating the spread

54
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:33,080
极端伊斯兰分子在非洲的扩散  肆虐
of Islamic radicalism throughout the continent.

55
00:03:33,230 --> 00:03:35,690
要做到这点  我们得做他们的盟友
And in order to achieve that, we need to work as its ally,

56
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,360
而不是监督人
not its disciplinarian.

57
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,760
早上好
Good morning.

58
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:43,120
总统先生
Mr. President.

59
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,530
杰姬
Jackie.

60
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,450
泰瑞
Terry.

61
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:49,860
坐吧
Shall we?

62
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:53,210
大纲你们都有了  今天要谈的是
Now you all have the, uh... overview. But what we have here today

63
00:03:53,210 --> 00:03:55,540
-细化过的...  -先生  开始之前
- is the comprehensive breakdown-- - Sir, before we begin--

64
00:03:55,540 --> 00:03:58,300
鲍勃  我知道你对法案还有疑虑
Look, Bob, I know you have some serious doubts about this program.

65
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:00,250
先让我把它亮出来
But just let me flesh it out first,

66
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:03,760
然后你有什么疑虑  我们再解决
and then I promise we can address any questions that you might have.

67
00:04:03,770 --> 00:04:06,300
-总统先生  -一千万个岗位
- Uh, Mr. President-- - Ten million jobs.

68
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:09,290
大家都同意这对国家是好事吧
Can we all agree that that's a good thing for this country?

69
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:10,750
保障全体就业
Universal employment.

70
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,700
这是2016年留在白宫的关键
It's the key for our keeping the White House in 2016.

71
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:16,900
也是唯一赢回国会多数席位的机会
It's the only chance we have of winning back majorities in Congress.

72
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:19,200
离大选只有18个月
Now, the election's only 18 months away.

73
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:22,200
我们得做点大胆  坚决的事
We need to do something bold, something decisive.

74
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:24,290
给我党改头换面
We need to redefine our party.

75
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:26,250
我们想说的就是这个
Actually, that's what we wanted to discuss.

76
00:04:26,260 --> 00:04:28,420
我党的确得改头换面
You're right, we do need to redefine the party.

77
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,930
换个新面孔
We need to do it with a fresh face.

78
00:04:29,930 --> 00:04:32,720
我们不希望您参加2016大选
2016. We don't want you to run.

79
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:34,980
您本就不是民选的总统
You weren't even elected to the office in the first place.

80
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:37,570
之前的赦免很致命  支持率非常低
The pardons hurt you. Approvals are low.

81
00:04:37,570 --> 00:04:38,970
我们不想怪谁  先生
We're not casting blame, sir.

82
00:04:38,970 --> 00:04:41,840
只是为党的利益考虑
We just believe that this is best for the party.

83
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:54,910
我猜到会有这一天  但不是这么快
I suspected this was coming, but months from now.

84
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:57,340
我还希望到时候能拿出点成绩
I was hoping by then I'd have something to show for my efforts,

85
00:04:57,340 --> 00:05:00,550
用进展打消他们的顾虑
that I could preempt their doubts with progress.

86
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:03,340
他们很紧张  这是冲动之举
They're nervous. They're being impulsive.

87
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,730
现在做这种决定太早了吧
It's a bit early to be deciding something like this.

88
00:05:05,730 --> 00:05:08,460
等初选临近了再考虑吧
Shouldn't we revisit this when we're closer to the primaries?

89
00:05:08,460 --> 00:05:10,050
你说呢  泰瑞
What do you think, Terry?

90
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:12,760
您也说了  我们离大选只有18个月了
Like you said, sir, we only have 18 months until the general.

91
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,940
离爱荷华州大选不到9个月了
Less than half of that to Iowa.

92
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:15,800
我们想尽快确定候选人
We would want to settle on a candidate soon.

93
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,370
全党一致支持的人
Someone who the whole party can get behind

94
00:05:17,370 --> 00:05:19,300
就像共和党的门多萨
like the Republicans are getting behind Mendoza.

95
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:20,560
是谁呢
And who would that be?

96
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,040
还没讨论过
We haven't had a discussion on that yet.

97
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:24,500
我们出于尊重  先来找您
We came to you first, out of respect.

98
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:27,780
-总有几个人选吧  -还没有
- Well, there must be a shortlist. - No, not yet.

99
00:05:28,050 --> 00:05:30,430
找到合适人选需要时间
It'll be a process to find the right person.

100
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:32,870
而我们希望您也能参与其中
And we were hoping that you would be a part of that process.

101
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:35,350
当然了我们只是请求  总统先生
Obviously, this is a request, Mr. President.

102
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:37,010
拍板的还是您
It's your decision.

103
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:40,580
但如果您决定参选  恕我们不能支持
But if you do run, sir, you won't have our support.

104
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:42,930
杰姬
Jackie?

105
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:47,650
我支持领导层的决定
I stand by the rest of the leadership.

106
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,230
好吧  还有许多事需要考虑
Well, this is certainly a lot to think about.

107
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:56,170
我们改天再聊《美国就业法案》的事
Let's table our discussion on America Works for another time,

108
00:05:56,170 --> 00:05:58,250
不过感谢各位如此直率
but thank you all for being so forthright.

109
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:00,600
我稍后会就此问题给你们答复
I'll get back to you on this issue a little later on.

110
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,490
您介不介意我们先逗留一阵子
Would you like us to stick around for a while?

111
00:06:02,490 --> 00:06:04,650
我们可不希望媒体觉得我们特地来跑一趟
We wouldn't want the press to think we came all the way here

112
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:06,990
-就为了五分钟的小会  -好想法
- for a five-minute meeting. - That's a very good idea.

113
00:06:06,990 --> 00:06:08,220
不能引起非议
No raised eyebrows.

114
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:11,300
我会叫人送茶点到地图室的
I'll have some refreshments sent for you into the Map Room.

115
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,270
很好
Wonderful.

116
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:13,810
谢谢您  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

117
00:06:23,140 --> 00:06:26,910
作为上次会议性侵法案的主要支持者
As a vocal proponent for the Sexual Assault Bill last session,

118
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:29,530
你是否担忧你和美国军队的关系
are you concerned about your relationship with the US military?

119
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:30,730
我并不担心  参议员
No, I'm not, Senator.

120
00:06:30,730 --> 00:06:33,400
我和参联会在那项法案上合作密切
I worked closely with the Joint Chiefs on that bill.

121
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:36,460
假设现在缅甸有一项维和行动
What if there were a peacekeeping mission in, say, Burma,

122
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:38,210
镇压平民暴动
to quell civil unrest,

123
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:41,770
联合国要求我国出兵
and the United Nations asked us to contribute troops,

124
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:44,290
让我们的男女士兵冒生命危险
to put our servicemen and women's lives in peril.

125
00:06:44,290 --> 00:06:46,330
如果您用缅甸做假设的话
If you're using Myanmar as a hypothetical,

126
00:06:46,330 --> 00:06:48,590
我觉得这一段时间内还不会发生  不过作为大使
I think we're a long way from that, but as Ambassador--

127
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:51,670
我的问题关注的是美国军力的使用
My question concerns the use of US military.

128
00:06:51,980 --> 00:06:54,600
美军是无关紧要的  缅甸的现状是...
The US military is irrelevant. The current situation--

129
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:58,250
抱歉  安德伍德夫人  美军无关紧要吗
Excuse me, Mrs. Underwood. The US military is irrelevant?

130
00:06:58,540 --> 00:07:00,220
我不是这个意思
Well, I-- That's not what I said.

131
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:03,010
这是你的原话  "美军是无关紧要的"
You said verbatim: "The US military is irrelevant."

132
00:07:03,010 --> 00:07:06,390
我所想表达的意思是...
Well, in the, in the context of-- I meant...

133
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:08,220
这其中有许多...
uh, that there are plenty--

134
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:12,760
我对美国军人无比尊敬  先生
I have the utmost respect and appreciation for our troops, sir.

135
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:14,480
你这话可不像是有多尊敬
Not with statements like that, you don't.

136
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,040
参议员  请允许我解释
Senator, if I may, I can explain.

137
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,920
我们该怎么向海外服役的男女士兵
How do we explain to the men and women who serve,

138
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,300
那些出生入死的人解释
who put their lives on the line,

139
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:22,270
我们驻联合国的大使认为他们无关紧要
that our ambassador thinks they're irrelevant?

140
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:25,010
我觉得您这样说实在是曲解了我的本意
I think that's an unfair characterization of what I intended--

141
00:07:25,010 --> 00:07:27,460
我可没有曲解什么  安德伍德夫人
I am not characterizing anything, Mrs. Underwood,

142
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:28,540
话是你自己说的
you said the words.

143
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:30,240
而现在你又想耍花招赖掉自己的话
And now you're trying to backpedal your way out of it.

144
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,030
-您就是在断章取义  -不要打断我
- You're trying to take my words-- - Don't interrupt me.

145
00:07:32,030 --> 00:07:33,760
如果您能不打断我的话  我可以解释的
If you will stop interrupting me, I can explain--

146
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:36,040
瞧  问问题的是我们  你只管回答
No, you see, we ask the questions, you answer them.

147
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,650
而您就是不让我好好回答问题  参议员
You're not allowing me to answer the questions, Senator.

148
00:07:38,650 --> 00:07:41,650
您只顾着哗众取宠  就是不肯听我讲
If you could maybe listen instead of grandstanding.

149
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:46,550
你此次应征的职位
The position you're being considered for

150
00:07:46,660 --> 00:07:48,900
要求你有冷静沉稳的外交手段
requires calm, cool diplomacy.

151
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:52,890
相比你对军方的言论
What concerns me even more than the military comment

152
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:54,230
我们更担心你的举止
is your demeanor.

153
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:58,150
我们就要让你这样的人去当大使吗
Is this what we're to expect from our ambassador?

154
00:07:58,150 --> 00:07:59,220
一个急性子
A hothead?

155
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,580
那请吧  安德伍德夫人  我洗耳恭听
Go ahead, Mrs. Underwood, I'm listening.

156
00:08:06,610 --> 00:08:08,450
也许他们别有所图
Maybe it's leverage for another play.

157
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:10,300
先吓破我的胆  然后漫天要价
Scare the wits out of me and then come with the big ask.

158
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:11,740
你确定他们有价码吗
You sure there is one?

159
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:13,620
他们想毙掉《美国就业法案》
America Works. They want to kill it.

160
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:16,640
或者逼我考虑换一个总统竞选搭档
Or soften me up to consider another VP candidate for the ticket.

161
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,170
他们不喜欢布莱斯
They're no fans of Blythe.

162
00:08:18,170 --> 00:08:20,030
什么事都有可能  没准要求多着呢
Could be anything, any combination of things.

163
00:08:20,030 --> 00:08:21,870
-怎么了  -您还没看到吗
- What? - You saw it?

164
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:24,640
-看到什么  -第一夫人  先生
- Saw what? - The First Lady, sir.

165
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:30,540
第一夫人称  美军无关紧要

166
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:29,810
天啊
Jesus.

167
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:31,120
第一夫人称  美军无关紧要

168
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:31,920
我得赶紧打给她
I better call her.

169
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:31,460
第一夫人称  美军无关紧要

170
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,560
她还在参加听证
She's still in the hearing, sir.

171
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:36,190
我要把整个过程看一遍  最好提前想想对策
I need to see this whole thing. Let's get ahead of it if we can.

172
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:38,290
-副检察长到了  -取消会面
- The Solicitor General is here. - Cancel it.

173
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,220
-您已经推迟两次了  -那再推迟一次
- You've already postponed twice. - Postpone it again.

174
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:41,220
不能再推迟了  先生
We can't put it off, sir.

175
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:42,870
还有不到一个月就要上最高法院了
It goes to the Supreme Court in less than a month.

176
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,230
我们有更大的事要处理
We have bigger fish to fry.

177
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:46,650
一名美国公民在无人机袭击中受伤
An American citizen was injured by a drone strike.

178
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,420
那是沃克下的令  不是我
That Walker authorized, not me.

179
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:49,970
但你是在任总统
But you're the sitting president.

180
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,570
如果处理不力  对你的权威会有极大损害
If we lose this, it undermines your authority.

181
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:53,810
媒体报道铺天盖地
The media is all over it.

182
00:08:53,810 --> 00:08:56,100
我们必须跟副检察长统一说辞
We need our rhetoric in line with the Solicitor General's.

183
00:08:56,100 --> 00:08:57,830
行了  老天爷  让她进来
All right. Christ! Send her in.

184
00:08:57,830 --> 00:09:00,530
我会把片段放到您电脑上  方便您查阅
I'll put this clip on your computer, for when you're done.

185
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:04,330
私下联系泰瑞·乌麦克  我今天就要见他
Terry Womack. Today. Privately.

186
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:22,670
邓巴女士
Ms. Dunbar.

187
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:29,330
在我们开始前  有些话我要说清楚
Before we begin, I'd like to clear the air.

188
00:09:29,930 --> 00:09:33,770
你的报告真的非常好  非常必要
Your report. You did good work, necessary work,

189
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:35,700
我对此表示敬意
and I admire you for it.

190
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:37,550
谢谢您的肯定  先生
I appreciate you saying that, sir.

191
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:40,200
你也理解我下达赦免令的考虑
And you understand the position I was in with the pardons.

192
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,380
那是政治问题  我不在行
That's politics, sir. Not my expertise.

193
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:45,140
那我们既往不咎了吗
What's past is past?

194
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:48,290
我关注的是要在法庭上说什么
My focus is the argument I'll present to the court.

195
00:09:50,990 --> 00:09:54,110
她觉得我就是抢了银行逃到郡界的劫匪
She sees me as the bank robber who made it to the county line.

196
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:57,570
但她很聪明  没把这态度带进门
But she's smart enough to leave her badge at the door.

197
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:59,630
那么  这案子
So, the case.

198
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:02,950
先生  我们觉得以国家机密来辩护十分可行
As you know, sir, we think the State secret defense is strong.

199
00:10:02,950 --> 00:10:04,850
我与中情局商议时...
When I consulted with the CIA on the--

200
00:10:04,850 --> 00:10:08,280
我在想用国家机密做辩护是不是最好的策略
I'm wondering if State secrets is the best tactic.

201
00:10:08,690 --> 00:10:11,190
默罕默德的两条腿都被截肢了
Both of Mahmoud's legs were amputated.

202
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:13,810
他会坐在轮椅上  出现在旁听席
He will be in the gallery, in his wheelchair.

203
00:10:13,810 --> 00:10:15,460
这画面非常震撼
That's a powerful image.

204
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:18,360
就算是最高法院法官也会心软
Even Supreme Court Justices have hearts.

205
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:20,410
我们得让他们理性思考
We need to stay in their heads.

206
00:10:20,410 --> 00:10:22,800
诉讼程序显然...
A procedural route is clearly-- -

207
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:23,890
稍等
Excuse me.

208
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,400
是的
Yes?

209
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:29,790
告诉她我得看点东西
Uh, tell her I need to watch something

210
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:32,160
两分钟后在书房给她回电
and I'll call her back from my study in two minutes.

211
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,750
-是我夫人  抱歉  -没关系
- It's my wife. I'm sorry. - Please.

212
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,270
-你只管回答  -而您就是不让我
- ...you answer them. - You're not allowing me

213
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,320
好好回答问题  参议员  
to answer questions, Senator.

214
00:10:48,330 --> 00:10:49,470
您只顾着哗众取宠
Maybe you would benefit more

215
00:10:49,470 --> 00:10:51,500
就是不肯听我讲
from listening than grandstanding.

216
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:58,020
我刚看完  我能做什么
I just watched. How can I help?

217
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,690
我在给各个参议员打电话
I'm calling Senators.

218
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:02,200
如果你也给他们打就太过了
I think it would be heavy-handed if you did too.

219
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,950
你生气我能理解
Well, I don't blame you for getting upset.

220
00:11:03,950 --> 00:11:06,070
-你不应该受如此对待  -我成靶子了
- You didn't deserve that. - I'm a target now.

221
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:09,000
-这是从政的代价  -我们都是靶子
- That's the price of admission. - We both are.

222
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:12,930
领导层不希望我参加竞选
The leadership, they don't want me to run.

223
00:11:12,930 --> 00:11:14,540
-什么  -他们是这么说的
- What? - Yeah, that's what they said

224
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:16,670
我都没来得及拿出法案
before I could even present the program.

225
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:19,770
-这么快吗  -是啊  我也很惊讶
- This soon? - Yeah, that's what surprised me.

226
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:23,710
-整个领导层吗  -所有人  包括杰姬
- The entire leadership? - All of them, including Jackie.

227
00:11:26,850 --> 00:11:30,330
-这女人毫无忠心  -等着看吧
- That woman has no sense of loyalty. - Well, we'll see.

228
00:11:30,330 --> 00:11:32,800
我要和乌麦克见面  让他改主意
I'm gonna meet with Womack. Turn him around.

229
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,960
他们只是人多势众
They only have strength in numbers.

230
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:45,350
请继续
Continue, please.

231
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:49,230
正如之前所说  我们的程序性抗辩很可行
As I was saying, we think our procedural defense is strong.

232
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:51,870
国家机密不允许被用作证据
State secrets prohibit the introduction of evidence.

233
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:54,660
即使他们不直接撤案
Assuming they won't dismiss outright,

234
00:11:54,660 --> 00:11:57,910
辩论也会聚焦于遵从行政命令
the argument will focus on deference to the executive.

235
00:11:58,030 --> 00:12:01,060
法院和外交政策的独立性
Separation between the courts and foreign policy.

236
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:03,810
我们面对来自多领域的威胁
They simply don't have the security intelligence

237
00:12:03,810 --> 00:12:06,490
他们根本没有足够的安全情报
to second-guess covert operations

238
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:09,780
事后指戳秘密行动的合理性
while we're facing threats on multiple fronts.

239
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,850
先生
Sir?

240
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:19,060
-我现在无法处理  -您说什么  先生
- I can't do this now. - Excuse me, sir?

241
00:12:19,060 --> 00:12:22,270
我的办公室会与你联系  抱歉  谢谢
My office will be in touch. Apologies. Thank you very much.

242
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:28,230
您只顾着哗众取宠  就是不肯听我讲
Maybe you would benefit more from listening than grandstanding.

243
00:12:28,230 --> 00:12:29,490
欢迎收看CNN首席国会记者
Joining me now from Capitol Hill,

244
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:31,640
达娜·巴什从国会发来的报道
CNN's Chief Congressional Correspondent, Dana Bash.

245
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,780
达娜  现在国会意向如何
Dana, what is the mood at the Capitol?

246
00:12:33,780 --> 00:12:34,420
没错  我理解
Right, I understand, but...

247
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:36,520
已经有几位参议员公开表示
We already have several Senators publicly saying

248
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,430
由于安德伍德夫人的言论
that they're gonna vote against Mrs.Underwood

249
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:39,890
将会投票反对她
because of her comments.

250
00:12:39,890 --> 00:12:41,330
而另一些参议员
A number of others I've spoken to

251
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:42,100
从支持她
have gone from supporting her...

252
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,050
-好的  -转变为了持观望态度
- Right. - ...nomination, to being on the fence.

253
00:12:44,050 --> 00:12:46,190
但达娜  她说的对吧
But, Dana, she's correct, isn't she?

254
00:12:46,190 --> 00:12:48,140
门多萨就是在哗众取宠
Mendoza was grandstanding.

255
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:50,750
也许吧  但即便如此  看看支持率
Maybe. But even so, if you look at the numbers here,

256
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,040
这事杀伤力很大
this is doing real damage.

257
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:54,210
投票结果本就接近
The vote was always going to be close...

258
00:12:54,210 --> 00:12:54,950
是的
Yes.

259
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:57,720
第一夫人的形势可不太好
...things aren't looking good for the First Lady.

260
00:12:57,720 --> 00:13:00,280
-我明白  但  -她对美军的言论会是
- No, I understand, but-- - Could her military remark be...

261
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,170
-门多萨来电  -口误吗
- It's Mendoza. - ...a slip of the tongue?

262
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:05,500
感谢您接听  参议员  希望您能再考虑
I appreciate your time, Senator. I hope you'll reconsider.

263
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:07,480
-他在线吗  -没错
- He's on now? - Yes.

264
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:08,910
把电视关了
Turn that off?

265
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:13,070
参议员  感谢你回电
Senator, hi. Thank you for returning my call.

266
00:13:13,070 --> 00:13:16,180
抱歉让你等这么久  我要处理一堆采访
Sorry it took so long. I had a ton of interview requests.

267
00:13:16,180 --> 00:13:17,860
我想表示道歉
I just wanted to apologize

268
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:20,290
我今天无意失敬
if I came across as disrespectful in any way.

269
00:13:20,290 --> 00:13:21,200
我不该那么说
That was wrong of me.

270
00:13:21,210 --> 00:13:22,330
我知道你是无心的  克莱尔
I know you didn't mean it, Claire.

271
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:25,220
很不幸事情发展至此
It's just unfortunate how things are playing out.

272
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:28,930
我知道你本人不能给我投票
I realize you can't vote for me yourself,

273
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:30,160
但我希望也许
but I was hoping that maybe

274
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,140
你可以帮我说些好话
you would say something to the effect to--

275
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,500
什么  对媒体吗
What, to the press?

276
00:13:34,610 --> 00:13:37,550
-或者私下里  对你同事  -不行
- Or even privately, to your colleagues. - I can't do that.

277
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:40,270
参议员  投票应该注重于我的优点
Senator, the vote should center on my merits,

278
00:13:40,270 --> 00:13:42,930
而不是你我剑拔弩张的个别瞬间
not a few moments where you and I took the gloves off.

279
00:13:42,930 --> 00:13:44,270
我觉得这很能说明问题
Well, I think that was telling, don't you?

280
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:46,000
你面对压力时的反应
How you behaved under pressure?

281
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:50,330
参议员  你知道你是在断章取义吧
Senator, you know you were taking out of context what I said.

282
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:52,170
知道  我故意惹怒你的
Of course I was. I was trying to rile you up.

283
00:13:52,170 --> 00:13:53,600
我也成功了
And I succeeded.

284
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:54,660
我真后悔
I wish I hadn't,

285
00:13:54,660 --> 00:13:56,090
因为你现在的情况真的不乐观
because it's gonna make things really tough for you.

286
00:13:56,090 --> 00:13:58,630
但是如果你现在
But, if you can convince my

287
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:01,060
还能说服我的同事改变主意的话
colleagues to change their minds despite that...

288
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:03,230
你肯定能做个好大使的
why, you'd make a great Ambassador.

289
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:06,210
-叨扰了  参议员  -好运  克莱尔
- Thank you for your time, Senator. - Good luck, Claire.

290
00:14:08,330 --> 00:14:09,850
真是个王八蛋
He's a son of a bitch.

291
00:14:10,710 --> 00:14:12,330
试试彼得森
Let's try Peterson next.

292
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:14,810
支持率总会变化
Approvals go up and down.

293
00:14:14,810 --> 00:14:17,860
我们不能被公众的想法左右
We can't allow ourselves to be held hostage by public opinion.

294
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:20,360
是共和党在逼我们
We're being held hostage by the Republicans.

295
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,720
由你代表我党是击败不了他们的  就这样
We can't beat them with you as the face of the party. Period.

296
00:14:22,730 --> 00:14:24,740
你们真的考虑清楚了吗
Have you all really thought this through?

297
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,370
我是在任总统
I'm a sitting president.

298
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:27,820
但不是民选的
But not an elected one.

299
00:14:27,820 --> 00:14:29,810
但就这么放弃在任者
But still, to abandon the incumbent,

300
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:31,900
和其所代表的影响力吗
and all the advantages that that entails?

301
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:35,980
问题就在这儿  你没什么影响力了
Which is the problem. We don't see any advantages.

302
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:37,960
如果你跟我们的路线走
And if you were to come on board with us,

303
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,990
公开宣布你不参选
if you were to announce that you're not running,

304
00:14:39,990 --> 00:14:41,980
大家就不会觉得是我们抛弃了你
it wouldn't seem as if we're abandoning you.

305
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:44,050
党还是统一的
The party looks unified.

306
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:46,470
自从我强行通过教育法案
Bob Birch has been trying to do me in

307
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:48,970
鲍勃·博奇就一直计划着坑我一把
since I forced the Education Bill down his throat.

308
00:14:48,970 --> 00:14:51,590
他是在用站不住脚的道理说服你们
I think he's using shaky logic to get you all on board

309
00:14:51,590 --> 00:14:54,720
方便他向我寻仇
so he can carry out some personal vendetta.

310
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,370
是我的主意
It was my idea.

311
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,220
不是鲍勃的
Not Bob's.

312
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:05,180
希望你能跟我们合作
I hope you work with us.

313
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:07,850
我们说的是真心话
We meant it when we said it.

314
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:11,890
我们希望听取你的意见
We would like for you to be a part of the conversation.

315
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:27,160
-喂  -是我
- Hello? - Hey, it's me.

316
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:31,970
-我听不见  -等等
- I can't hear you. - Hang on a second.

317
00:15:39,350 --> 00:15:40,280
-赛斯吗  -对
- Seth? - Yeah.

318
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:42,780
我就想问问你有没有事
I was just calling to check in. See how things are going.

319
00:15:42,780 --> 00:15:44,380
没事  都挺好的
Good. Things are going really good.

320
00:15:44,380 --> 00:15:46,190
等一下
Hey, hold on one quick second.

321
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:55,160
我知道
Listen, uh, I know

322
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,320
你们要推出《美就法》项目了
you're rolling out the AmWorks program soon.

323
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,690
雷米肯定已经有了计划
I'm sure Remy has a plan in place,

324
00:15:58,690 --> 00:16:00,750
但我也列了个单子
but I've been putting together a list.

325
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:01,720
关键议员
Some key representatives

326
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:03,880
和他们可能开出的价码
and what they might want in exchange for support.

327
00:16:03,890 --> 00:16:05,890
肮脏秘密什么的
Skeletons in the closet, that kind of thing.

328
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:07,730
那项法案现在搁置了
Yeah, that's on hold for the moment.

329
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,910
-不推出了吗  -就是暂时搁置了
- You're not rolling it out? - It's just on hold.

330
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,580
-出什么事了吗  -没什么事
- Is something up? - No, everything's fine.

331
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:18,180
现在的重点是下周俄罗斯的峰会
We're focused on the summit next month with Russia.

332
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:21,190
你还好吗  身体好起来了吗
But you're good? You getting stronger?

333
00:16:21,590 --> 00:16:23,650
-嗯  -精神呢
- Yeah. - In good spirits?

334
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:24,790
好得不得了
Never been better.

335
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,710
我发邮件给你  他的想法记得告诉我
I'll email you my ideas. Let me know what he says.

336
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:30,340
-没问题  -谢谢
- Will do. - Thanks.

337
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:35,930
参议员  上周在办公室见面时
Senator, when we met in your office last week,

338
00:16:35,930 --> 00:16:37,730
我们进行了一次很长很有成果的谈话
we had a long, productive conversation.

339
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:40,920
我觉得听证会上的十秒说明不...
I can't imagine ten seconds during the hearing would--

340
00:16:41,380 --> 00:16:44,120
参议员先生  我五分钟后再打过去好吗
Senator, may I call you back in five minutes?

341
00:16:44,410 --> 00:16:45,390
谢谢
Thank you.

342
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,780
-弗兰西斯  -不行  根本是他的主意
- Francis? - No luck. It was his idea.

343
00:16:56,170 --> 00:16:57,270
你打算怎么做
What are you going to do?

344
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:59,870
找上次竞选前50的资助人
Top 50 bundlers from last cycle.

345
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:02,120
控制了资金我就不必靠领导层了
I don't need the leadership if I can get the money.

346
00:17:02,150 --> 00:17:03,520
-你呢  -还没准
- You? - Too early to tell.

347
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,180
我就在这儿  需要就来找我
Well, I'm here if you need me.

348
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:12,210
我一直说权力比金钱重要
I've always said that power is more important than money.

349
00:17:12,210 --> 00:17:15,550
但竞选的时候  金钱才能让权力
But when it comes to elections, money gives power...

350
00:17:16,070 --> 00:17:18,010
有竞争力
well, a run for its money.

351
00:17:19,380 --> 00:17:20,760
弗兰西斯·安德伍德
It's Francis Underwood.

352
00:17:30,460 --> 00:17:31,840
你说他挺帅的来着
I thought you said he was handsome.

353
00:17:33,180 --> 00:17:34,520
抱歉打扰了
Sorry to interrupt.

354
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:38,280
如果她没收到说有"急事"的短信
Well, if she doesn't receive a text with the word "urgent,"

355
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,020
那就算不上约会了
it's not an official date.

356
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:42,010
你好  艾伦·库克
How are you? Alan Cooke.

357
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:43,880
-雷米·丹顿  -幸会
- Remy Danton. - Nice to meet you.

358
00:17:44,890 --> 00:17:47,070
我去...打几个电话
I'm just gonna go, uh... take a few calls.

359
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:49,870
我替你点了杯咖啡
There's an espresso coming with your name on it, okay?

360
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:50,810
再会
Nice meeting you.

361
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:57,860
说说吧
So here we are.

362
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:01,050
我没有参与  会面十分钟前他们才通知我
I wasn't part of the decision. They told me ten minutes before.

363
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:03,300
他们都找谁谈竞选的事了
Who are they talking to? About running?

364
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:05,240
据我所知还没有
No one yet, as far as I can tell.

365
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:08,330
总得有个名单  哪怕还没说出来
There has to at least be a list. Even a mental one.

366
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,810
有些想法
Some ideas.

367
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:12,580
我们需要你查出来
We need you to find out.

368
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,030
沃克辞职的时候
You know, when Walker resigned,

369
00:18:16,510 --> 00:18:19,110
弗兰克就任总统  你是幕僚长
Frank's president, you're Chief of Staff.

370
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:21,560
-我呢  -你还在领导层
- But me? - You're still in the leadership.

371
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:24,430
-助理党鞭  -就是扯淡
- Assistant Whip. - It's a bullshit title.

372
00:18:24,930 --> 00:18:26,660
我不在核心圈子里
I'm out of the inner circle.

373
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,790
那你要什么
What do you want?

374
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:34,960
我要做他的副总统
I want to be on the ticket. His VP.

375
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,390
我们只要一点点信息
All we want is a little information.

376
00:18:38,390 --> 00:18:42,470
你开的价  太高了吧
What you're asking is... disproportionate.

377
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:45,740
当做是还债了吧
It's repaying a debt.

378
00:18:46,570 --> 00:18:49,350
好大一笔债呢  弹劾法案是我搞定的
A big one. I whipped the votes for impeachment.

379
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:51,280
现在我要回报了
I should get to cash in on that.

380
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,300
他是不会同意的
There's no way he'll go for this.

381
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:56,720
那我也没必要做你们的眼线了
Then there's no reason for me to be your eyes and ears.

382
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:01,920
回头联系你
I'll get back to you.

383
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:04,920
要在工作时间
During business hours.

384
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:18,060
{\an3}艾拉·萨伊德

385
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:18,230
发送短信

386
00:19:18,060 --> 00:19:18,390
{\an3}艾拉·萨伊德

387
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:26,030
不  马克  就在白宫的决策室  我发誓
No, Mark, we ran it in the White House screening room and I swear to God,

388
00:19:26,030 --> 00:19:29,210
战斗机撞向海狼核潜艇的时候
when those jets crashed into one of our Seawolf subs,

389
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:31,170
参联会都喊出来了
the Joint Chiefs screamed.

390
00:19:32,230 --> 00:19:34,450
他们肯定不希望你用  更不会免费给你
No, they didn't want you to use it and certainly not for free.

391
00:19:34,450 --> 00:19:36,100
大卫  我不只是要钱
David, I'm not just asking you for money,

392
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:38,350
我希望你做我的竞选主席
I'm asking you to be one of my campaign chairmen.

393
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:41,040
那可比在总统卧室睡一晚风光多了
That buys you a lot more than a night in the Lincoln Bedroom.

394
00:19:43,330 --> 00:19:45,210
克莱尔·安德伍德找海尔布鲁克参议员
Claire Underwood for Senator Hylbrook.

395
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:48,310
我同意  肯定不能只靠安全委员会的支持
I agree. We can never rely solely upon Security Counsel support.

396
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:49,720
斯科特  还剩18个月了
Scott, we're 18 months out.

397
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,120
你想参与进来
Now, if you wanna be on the ground floor,

398
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,810
就别想占着茅坑不拉屎
you got to shit or get off the pot.

399
00:19:52,810 --> 00:19:56,390
关键是领导  做出榜样
The key is to provide leadership, to lead by example.

400
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:59,550
我还想着一起去梅德斯通打打高尔夫呢
I was hoping we could hit Maidstone for a quick eighteen.

401
00:19:59,940 --> 00:20:01,780
当然不  我打得可差了
No, I'm a terrible golfer.

402
00:20:01,790 --> 00:20:04,170
是啊  你就可以打败总统了
Exactly, you'd have the pleasure of beating a president.

403
00:20:04,170 --> 00:20:05,530
以后跟人可有得讲了
Now wouldn't that be a good cocktail story?

404
00:20:05,530 --> 00:20:08,650
我和您委员会里的共和党人差不多都谈过了
I've spoken to almost every Republican in your committee, sir.

405
00:20:09,490 --> 00:20:11,800
他们说都听您的
Yes, they're taking their cue from you.

406
00:20:14,370 --> 00:20:16,540
还有别的号码可以联系上他吗
Is there another number where I can reach him?

407
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:18,770
我今晚一定要跟他谈谈
It's important that we speak this evening.

408
00:20:20,490 --> 00:20:22,850
是的  不管多晚
Yes, anytime, no matter how late.

409
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:25,770
汤姆  我只希望你多点信心
A little faith, Tom. That's all I'm asking.

410
00:20:25,770 --> 00:20:29,660
是啊  我也不喜欢别人叫我女士
Oh, yes! I know, I don't like being called "Ma'am" Either.

411
00:20:30,010 --> 00:20:32,290
要是我做什么事都得哄大伙开心
If I made every decision based on what makes people feel good,

412
00:20:32,290 --> 00:20:34,360
那我就去主持脱口秀了  当什么总统
I'd be a talk show host, not the president.

413
00:20:34,370 --> 00:20:36,460
我知道詹宁斯上将是你的好朋友
Well, I know Admiral Jennings is a good friend of yours,

414
00:20:36,460 --> 00:20:38,910
-我可以亲自打给他  -别被恐惧左右
- I can call him personally. - Don't let fear drive you.

415
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,250
你的生意不是这么做出来的吧
That's not how you run your business, is it?

416
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:41,790
我知道你也曾被人曲解
I know you've been in my shoes,

417
00:20:41,790 --> 00:20:43,170
那种断章取义不是我们本意
and sound bites are not who we are.

418
00:20:43,170 --> 00:20:44,400
那是省小钱吃大亏
Penny-wise and pound-foolish.

419
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,890
抱歉  参议员  吵醒你了吗
I'm so sorry, Senator, did I wake you?

420
00:20:47,740 --> 00:20:49,900
好的  没事  我明天再挂
Yes, no, I'll try back again tomorrow.

421
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:52,060
你目光短浅我不怪你
I can't fault you for being shortsighted.

422
00:20:52,070 --> 00:20:54,740
但我记性好你也别怪我
I hope you won't fault me for having a long memory.

423
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:55,740
晚安
Good night!

424
00:20:59,910 --> 00:21:03,250
已经有人睡了  我明早再试
I'm waking people up now. I'll start again in the morning.

425
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:08,420
-怎么样  -一点也说不准
- How's it looking? - I had to flip a coin? I don't know.

426
00:21:09,150 --> 00:21:12,070
-你呢  -还没人支持我
- You? - Not a single backer yet.

427
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:14,080
-一个都没有吗  -加州那边还早
- Not one? - California's still awake.

428
00:21:14,090 --> 00:21:15,860
也许我在西海岸运气能好点
Maybe I'll have better luck out west.

429
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:18,110
我出去跑一圈  我得做点什么
I'm going for a run. I need to do something.

430
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,940
-太晚了  -我闲不下来了
- It's late. - Well, I'm too restless.

431
00:21:19,940 --> 00:21:23,360
那我一个人在这儿吃晚饭了
Well, I'll be here, singing for my supper.

432
00:21:29,540 --> 00:21:32,410
求个脸书上的毛头小子
It's humiliating to have to beg from some kid who was on Facebook

433
00:21:32,410 --> 00:21:34,800
实在丢人  但那是...
before his testicles descended, but that's--

434
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:38,010
德里克  弗兰西斯·安德伍德  有时间吗
Derrick, Francis Underwood. Do you have a few minutes?

435
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:41,790
我绕着国家广场跑
I'll be running along the Mall tonight.

436
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,530
那要出动全套安保
That requires a full detail.

437
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,500
你们多久能准备好
How soon can you be ready?

438
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,740
我们更希望您在附近跑
We'd far prefer you ran on the track.

439
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:49,400
我去国家广场跑
I'll be running along the Mall.

440
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:53,570
好的  夫人  第一夫人安保尽快出动
Yes, ma'am. We're going to need the First Lady's detail, ASAP.

441
00:21:56,340 --> 00:21:58,490
-不可公开  -可以
- This is off the record. - Agreed.

442
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,560
过去六个月
You've called my office every day

443
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:03,820
你一直给我办公室打电话  问同一个问题
for the last six months with one question.

444
00:22:03,820 --> 00:22:05,860
领导层的人我都联系过
I call everyone in the leadership.

445
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:08,100
得到的都是同一套说辞
I get the same non-answer from all of you:

446
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,920
"弗兰克·安德伍德是现任总统"
"Frank Underwood is our president..."

447
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,230
我们是他坚实的后盾
He has our undivided support.

448
00:22:12,230 --> 00:22:13,140
博奇有次说错了
Birch slipped up once.

449
00:22:13,140 --> 00:22:15,980
他说"不可动摇"不是"坚实"
He said "unwavering" instead of "undivided."

450
00:22:16,170 --> 00:22:17,820
我还以为他嗑药了
I wanted to drug-test him.

451
00:22:18,030 --> 00:22:20,390
今早在白宫有过一次会面
There was a meeting this morning in the White House.

452
00:22:21,210 --> 00:22:22,880
你们出来时我看到了
I was there on Pebble Beach when you came out.

453
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:25,260
一共就谈了四分半
It lasted four and a half minutes.

454
00:22:25,270 --> 00:22:28,320
-你们进去了一个小时  -是待了一个小时
- You were in there for an hour. - We were inside for an hour.

455
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:30,380
但不代表就谈了一个小时
Doesn't mean the meeting lasted that long.

456
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,480
发生什么了  为什么这么快
What happened? Why so short?

457
00:22:36,050 --> 00:22:37,910
你入围过普利策奖呢
You're the Pulitzer finalist.

458
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,170
《美国就业法案》吗
America Works?

459
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:43,040
总统下午是为了这个去的国会山吗
Is that why the president went to the Capitol this afternoon?

460
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,830
白宫的人都不松口
No one from the White House would say.

461
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,200
晚安
Have a good night.

462
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,670
你选了我  你想干什么
You chose me. What's your play?

463
00:22:56,820 --> 00:22:59,480
只要是写总统的  人们都会关注
When you write about presidents, people pay attention.

464
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:15,940
得最后定胜负了
It'll come down to the wire.

465
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:19,510
我有信心  但我也不希望有什么事听天由命
I'm confident, but I don't want to leave anything to chance.

466
00:25:20,810 --> 00:25:25,090
据艾瑞克森的消息  我今早有47票了
Well, according to Erikson, I have 47 votes as of this morning.

467
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:28,110
我知道  参议员  但那还不够
Well, I know, Senator, but that's not enough.

468
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:29,590
我还需要您的票
I need yours.

469
00:25:39,910 --> 00:25:43,500
我绝对是要竞选总统的
I have every intention of running for president.

470
00:25:43,860 --> 00:25:45,710
我得确定你们是支持我的
I need to know you two are with me.

471
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:48,630
有任何疑虑  就现在说出来
If you have any doubts, now's the time to let me know.

472
00:25:56,790 --> 00:25:59,230
南茜  清空时间表
Nancy, wipe the schedule clean.

473
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:00,590
全推掉
Yes, everything.

474
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,300
不讨论出个计划就不出去
We don't leave this office until we have a plan.

475
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:09,260
夫人  复活节滚彩蛋游戏的事
Ma'am? The Easter Egg Roll we were scheduled for?

476
00:26:09,260 --> 00:26:10,940
-是啊  -如果不方便...
- Right. - If this is a bad time...

477
00:26:10,940 --> 00:26:13,030
没什么  进来吧
No, that's fine. Please, come in.

478
00:26:14,070 --> 00:26:14,870
你好
Hello?

479
00:26:14,870 --> 00:26:17,700
是的  克莱尔·安德伍德  他在等我电话
Yes... Claire Underwood. He's expecting my call.

480
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:21,250
你好  希拉  真美
Hi, Sheila. They're beautiful.

481
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:22,410
摆一下好吗
Would you mind setting them up, please?

482
00:26:22,410 --> 00:26:24,470
我还要打几个电话
I have a couple more calls to make.

483
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:29,280
参议员  我挺好  您好吗
Hello, Senator. Yes, I'm well. How are you?

484
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:33,820
提名华盛顿特区克莱尔·安德伍德
The nomination of Claire Underwood, of Washington DC,

485
00:26:33,820 --> 00:26:35,100
担任美利坚合众国
to be the Representative of

486
00:26:35,110 --> 00:26:38,070
驻联合国代表
the United States of America to the United Nations.

487
00:26:38,070 --> 00:26:41,540
请听书记官喊名字  投赞成和反对
Yeas and nays have been ordered and the clerk will call the roll.

488
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:44,010
-阿博纳先生  -赞成
- Mr. Abner. - Yea.

489
00:26:44,930 --> 00:26:45,970
博朗先生
Mr. Braun.

490
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:48,560
布雷先生
Mr. Bray.

491
00:26:49,930 --> 00:26:53,370
-这个太粉了  -小姑娘都喜欢粉色
- This one's a little too pink. - Girls like pink.

492
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:55,580
这可不止是粉色了  几乎是霓虹色了
This is more than pink. It's neon.

493
00:26:56,390 --> 00:26:58,440
-我要选四个吗  -是的  夫人
- Uh, I'm choosing four? - Yes, ma'am.

494
00:26:58,510 --> 00:27:01,320
-薇拉  -领先两票  48对46
- Willa? - Up by two: 48 to 46.

495
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,460
-夫人  我们可以稍后再做  -不用
- Ma'am, we can finish up later. - No.

496
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:05,770
-下面呢  -纪念彩蛋
- Uh, what's next? - The commemoratives.

497
00:27:05,770 --> 00:27:07,380
都很特别
These are really special.

498
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:09,030
黑蛋吗
A black egg?

499
00:27:09,030 --> 00:27:12,330
-有爱国元素点缀  -那也是黑蛋
- Yes, with patriotic tipping. - It's still a black egg.

500
00:27:12,330 --> 00:27:14,310
刻着美国总统与第一夫人的签名
Engraved with POTUS and FLOTUS signatures.

501
00:27:14,310 --> 00:27:17,710
夫人  最后结果  52对48
Ma'am? Final tally: 52 to 48.

502
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:18,850
反对占多
Against.

503
00:27:25,990 --> 00:27:28,240
-媒体呢  -在通气室
- The press? - In the briefing room.

504
00:27:30,390 --> 00:27:32,950
我就回来  稍等一下好吗
I'll just be a few minutes. Would you mind waiting?

505
00:27:32,950 --> 00:27:34,050
当然  夫人
Not at all, ma'am.

506
00:27:47,060 --> 00:27:48,420
我听说了
I just heard.

507
00:27:49,750 --> 00:27:51,380
真遗憾
I'm so sorry.

508
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:53,160
媒体等着呢
The press is waiting.

509
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:54,670
他们等去吧
Well, they can wait.

510
00:27:55,190 --> 00:27:56,090
要我陪你去吗
Do you want me to come with you?

511
00:27:56,090 --> 00:27:58,310
不用  我就想尽快了事
No. I just want to get it over with.

512
00:28:00,710 --> 00:28:02,980
克莱尔  你...
Claire. You--

513
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:12,840
早上好
Good morning.

514
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:15,510
参议院没有通过我的提名  
Naturally, I'm disappointed

515
00:28:15,510 --> 00:28:18,770
我自然很失望
that the Senate did not confirm my nomination today.

516
00:28:19,190 --> 00:28:22,510
但能得到这个机会  我已经很感激
But I'm very grateful to have been afforded the opportunity.

517
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:25,260
我自然要谢谢我的丈夫
I'd be remiss if I did not thank my husband

518
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:27,730
感谢他对我的支持与信任
for all the faith and trust he placed in me.

519
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:31,120
他一向支持我实现梦想
He's always supported me in achieving my goals.

520
00:28:32,020 --> 00:28:36,240
我期待继续履行第一夫人的职责
I look forward to continued service as First Lady.

521
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:37,640
谢谢
Thank you.

522
00:28:53,010 --> 00:28:56,990
选绿的  蓝的  和米色的吧
Um, let's go with the... green, the blue, and the cream.

523
00:28:56,990 --> 00:29:00,070
纪念彩蛋呢  可以说是金券
And for the rare one? The Golden Ticket, so to speak?

524
00:29:01,050 --> 00:29:03,380
红的  红的好看
Red. That one's beautiful.

525
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:06,450
谢谢  我先走了
Thank you. Excuse me, please?

526
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,650
你试过吗
You ever try to do this?

527
00:29:33,430 --> 00:29:34,690
让蛋立住
Balance an egg?

528
00:29:37,370 --> 00:29:38,870
我们小时候常玩
We used to do this as kids.

529
00:29:48,030 --> 00:29:50,940
物理法则是没法改的吧
You can't change the laws of physics, can you?

530
00:30:04,450 --> 00:30:07,760
我错了  太难了
I was wrong. It's too hard.

531
00:30:07,790 --> 00:30:08,540
先生
Sir?

532
00:30:08,730 --> 00:30:11,690
对抗领导层  筹集竞选资金
Fighting the leadership, raising money.

533
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:14,010
不能强迫他们做极不情愿的事
We can't get them to do what they're dead set against doing.

534
00:30:14,010 --> 00:30:17,120
现在是负分  要拉到零都需要六个月
We'd need six months just to get them back to square one.

535
00:30:28,050 --> 00:30:30,380
得逆向思维
We have to reverse our thinking.

536
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,790
当强风袭来的时候
When the wind's blowing at gale force,

537
00:30:36,790 --> 00:30:39,160
没有必要逆风航行
there's no point in sailing against it.

538
00:30:41,950 --> 00:30:43,170
您有什么主意
What do you have in mind?

539
00:31:13,010 --> 00:31:15,080
请接白宫法律顾问办公室
The White House Counsel's office, please.

540
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:16,440
我不管他们有什么安排
I don't care about their schedules.

541
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:17,790
今天凑不齐那就明天早上
If not today, tomorrow morning.

542
00:31:17,790 --> 00:31:19,020
我们还请杰姬来吗
Should I invite Jackie, too?

543
00:31:19,020 --> 00:31:20,920
她毕竟还算是领导层里的
Well, she qualifies as leadership.

544
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:23,030
-那她的条件呢  -先拖着
- What about her ask? - Stall her for now.

545
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:24,780
看看会面怎样再说
Let's see how the meeting goes.

546
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:27,280
你给我写份讲稿  要字斟句酌
I want you to write the speech, every word.

547
00:31:27,290 --> 00:31:28,870
-好的  先生  -不得外泄
- Yes, sir. - And no leaks.

548
00:31:28,870 --> 00:31:30,850
三小时内给您草稿
You'll have a draft in three hours.

549
00:31:31,540 --> 00:31:35,570
另外  道格给我发了份《美就法》的游说策略
And, sir... Doug emailed me a lobbying strategy for AmWorks.

550
00:31:35,570 --> 00:31:37,440
-您要看一看吗  -他自己写的吗
- Do you want to look at it? - Of his own accord?

551
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:39,270
-你没告诉他吧  -我什么都没说
- You didn't tell him? - No, I didn't say a word.

552
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:41,240
肯定是他看新闻自己琢磨出来的
It must be what he gathered from watching the news.

553
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:44,390
-他怎样了  -道格听起来还行
- How is he? - Uh, Doug seems fine.

554
00:31:44,390 --> 00:31:46,110
按您的要求  我一直在给他打电话
I've been calling him, like you asked.

555
00:31:46,580 --> 00:31:48,590
-但他看起来如何  -他告诉我一切都好
- But he seems all right? - Well, he tells me things are good,

556
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,000
不过我估计就算不好他也不会说的
although I don't think he'd admit it if they weren't.

557
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,290
不如你抽空去看看他  我抽不出身
Why don't you stop by from time to time, since I can't.

558
00:31:54,290 --> 00:31:55,800
-要亲眼见到他  -好的  先生
- See him in person. - Yes, sir.

559
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:56,990
把他的策略转给我
And send me his email.

560
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:08,880
克莱尔
Claire?

561
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:15,570
如果你找我  我就在书房
I'll be in my study if you need me.

562
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:22,840
你忙什么呢
What're you working on?

563
00:32:24,450 --> 00:32:26,970
-给你带了杯咖啡  -你可救了我的命了
- Brought you a coffee. - My savior.

564
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,230
党领导层昨天开了个会
The leadership meeting yesterday morning.

565
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:31,100
只持续了四分半
It lasted four and a half minutes.

566
00:32:31,470 --> 00:32:32,350
你从哪听说的
Where'd you hear that?

567
00:32:32,350 --> 00:32:34,990
这么重大的内政议题不可能这么快就否了
That's not long enough to reject a major domestic agenda.

568
00:32:35,870 --> 00:32:38,150
我又没出席  我怎么知道会开了多久
I wasn't in the meeting. I don't know how long it lasted.

569
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:41,000
-出了什么事  -随你怎么说了
- Something went down. - If you say so.

570
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:42,970
反正我是什么都没听说
Uh, I didn't hear anything about it.

571
00:32:43,830 --> 00:32:45,810
没准是总统有急事先走了
Could've been the president was called away.

572
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:48,730
-经常这样  -这次不是
- That happens all the time. - Not this time.

573
00:32:49,190 --> 00:32:50,100
你怎么知道
How do you know?

574
00:32:50,650 --> 00:32:52,910
显然我有个知道的比你多的消息源
Clearly, I have a source that knows more than you.

575
00:32:53,700 --> 00:32:56,790
大多数消息源都这样  至少是假装这样
Most sources do. At least they pretend they do.

576
00:32:58,220 --> 00:32:59,350
多谢你的咖啡
Thanks for the coffee.

577
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:04,020
加两包糖  我下次会记得的
Two sugars next time. I'll remember that.

578
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,160
你和艾拉·萨伊德谈过了
You talked to Ayla Sayyad.

579
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:15,940
我既可以帮忙也可以帮倒忙
I can either be an asset or a liability.

580
00:33:16,510 --> 00:33:17,930
你以为这样就能保你成为竞选搭档了吗
You think this puts you on the ticket now?

581
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:19,310
你去告密的话自然不会了
Not if you tell him.

582
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:21,830
不过比较聪明的选择是替我说好话
But the smart move would be to advocate on my behalf.

583
00:33:21,830 --> 00:33:23,090
别逼我  杰姬
Don't strong-arm me, Jackie.

584
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:25,660
你是中间人  不逼你逼谁
You're the man in the middle. Who else would I strong-arm?

585
00:33:25,690 --> 00:33:27,590
我想成为你们的一员  雷米
I want to be on your team, Remy.

586
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,890
我们合作的时候结果一向不错
We do well when we're on the same team.

587
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:35,590
你还有别的电话吗
You have more calls?

588
00:33:36,770 --> 00:33:39,680
没有  忙完了
No. I'm done.

589
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:43,940
-谁向她泄密了  -我不知道  先生
- Who spoke to her? - I have no idea, sir.

590
00:33:43,940 --> 00:33:46,650
-你的工作就是知道  -事情发展太快
- Well, it's your job to know. - Things are moving fast.

591
00:33:46,650 --> 00:33:47,890
我只想尽力控制局面
I'm just trying to stay ahead of them.

592
00:33:47,890 --> 00:33:50,330
我们动作得再快点  会面定下来了吗
Well, we need to move faster. Has the meeting been set?

593
00:33:50,330 --> 00:33:52,960
明早8点  博奇的办公室刚给我回了话
Eight AM tomorrow. I just heard back from Birch's office.

594
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:55,190
很好  联系媒体准备好9点直播
Good. Let's have the networks ready to go live by nine.

595
00:33:55,190 --> 00:33:57,610
还有个问题  杰姬
One more thing. Jackie.

596
00:33:58,350 --> 00:34:00,270
我觉得你最好尽快做决定
I think you should decide sooner rather than later.

597
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:01,140
如果我们走这条路
If we're gonna go this route,

598
00:34:01,140 --> 00:34:02,310
就得争取尽可能多的友军
we need every ally we can get.

599
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:04,280
等开完会  我们再谈
After the meeting. We'll discuss then.

600
00:34:17,530 --> 00:34:19,030
你起来了啊
You've emerged.

601
00:34:22,620 --> 00:34:26,140
我小睡了一觉  昨晚我都没怎么睡
I took a nap. Last night was... I didn't get much sleep.

602
00:34:26,680 --> 00:34:27,670
我也是
Me, neither.

603
00:34:29,230 --> 00:34:30,980
我们肯定会给你找个职位的
We're gonna find something for you.

604
00:34:31,030 --> 00:34:35,250
其它的职位  或作为第一夫人的职责  我保证
Some other position, or something as First Lady, I promise.

605
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:37,030
我知道
I know.

606
00:34:38,650 --> 00:34:40,840
-你不睡做什么  -我在忙我的演说
- What are you doing up? - I've got to go over my speech.

607
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:43,020
我准备明晚发表演讲
It's happening tomorrow night.

608
00:34:43,070 --> 00:34:44,340
什么演讲
What speech?

609
00:34:56,680 --> 00:34:58,210
有点太急了  不是吗
It's premature, isn't it?

610
00:34:58,310 --> 00:34:59,240
读下去
Read on.

611
00:35:43,310 --> 00:35:44,220
好吗
Yes?

612
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,450
好
Yes.

613
00:35:52,530 --> 00:35:53,800
谢谢  请坐
Thank you. Please.

614
00:36:00,030 --> 00:36:03,330
你们的请求  我想了很多
I put a great deal of thought into what you've all asked of me.

615
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:06,430
我让自己尽量保持开放的态度
I challenged myself to keep an open mind.

616
00:36:07,020 --> 00:36:11,110
而我的决定是  我将不参选下任总统
And my decision is: I will not run for president.

617
00:36:12,010 --> 00:36:14,930
他们觉得这好的不真实  也的确不是真的
Look, they're thinking it's too good to be true, and it is.

618
00:36:14,930 --> 00:36:16,620
我之前在椭圆办公室撒过谎
I lied in the Oval Office before.

619
00:36:16,620 --> 00:36:18,270
这次不想再触霉头
I didn't want to take the chance this time.

620
00:36:18,270 --> 00:36:20,450
万一真说中了可不好
It's too big a deal to jinx myself.

621
00:36:20,910 --> 00:36:21,980
今晚9点
At nine o'clock tonight,

622
00:36:21,980 --> 00:36:24,490
我就向全国宣布我的决定
I will announce to the nation my decision.

623
00:36:24,490 --> 00:36:25,990
你什么目的
What's the catch?

624
00:36:27,570 --> 00:36:31,660
我要大家来这里见面是有原因的
I wanted us to meet here in this room for a reason.

625
00:36:32,030 --> 00:36:33,160
过去五个月
For the past five months,

626
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:37,000
我的团队就坐在这儿  起草《美国就业法案》
my team has sat at this very table, developing America Works.

627
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,190
你们知道这项目对我意义重大
You know how much the program means to me,

628
00:36:39,190 --> 00:36:40,720
我希望你们也能像我一样重视
and I want it to mean as much to you.

629
00:36:40,730 --> 00:36:43,910
-那你是有目的的了  -不  是机遇
- So there is a catch. - No, an opportunity.

630
00:36:43,910 --> 00:36:45,360
我们都知道
Look, we all know the--

631
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:49,500
单纯地打个比方
All right, let's just say for... argument's sake

632
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:50,720
这张桌子
that this table here

633
00:36:50,720 --> 00:36:53,500
就是未来一年半
represents the next year and a half, all right?

634
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:55,600
我们在这儿
So, this is us right now.

635
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:57,770
那边的尽头是大选
And down there at the end, that's the election.

636
00:36:57,780 --> 00:37:02,090
我要是决定竞选  接下来几个月我就得筹款
Now, if I did run, I'd spend the next few months fundraising.

637
00:37:02,090 --> 00:37:05,020
到这时左右  我要正式宣布
And then somewhere around here, I'd formally announce.

638
00:37:05,020 --> 00:37:06,850
哪怕我赢了党内竞选
And then even if I did win the nomination,

639
00:37:06,850 --> 00:37:08,540
比如说在这个时候
say, somewhere around here,

640
00:37:08,540 --> 00:37:10,140
我就得面对
I'd start to have to face off

641
00:37:10,140 --> 00:37:12,440
共和党的对手  很可能是门多萨
with a Republican challenger, probably Mendoza.

642
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:14,750
那可就是真刀真枪了
And then things would get brutal.

643
00:37:15,110 --> 00:37:16,900
每天都得去做活动
Daily, daily events.

644
00:37:16,970 --> 00:37:18,680
防御对手的进攻
Fending off attacks.

645
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:20,350
同时进攻对手
Launching my own.

646
00:37:20,380 --> 00:37:23,170
你们说得对
And... you're right.

647
00:37:23,170 --> 00:37:24,350
最后...
In the end...

648
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:26,780
...我可能会输
...I'd probably lose.

649
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:31,370
我会花18个月的时间竞选
I would spend 18 months campaigning,

650
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:34,890
就没有时间治国了
which would leave no time to govern.

651
00:37:36,780 --> 00:37:39,800
你们让我看清了局势
But you have opened my eyes.

652
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,850
解放了思想
I feel liberated.

653
00:37:41,850 --> 00:37:46,480
接下来的18个月我想专注一件事
I want to spend these next 18 months dedicated to one thing:

654
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:49,560
《美国就业法案》  但我需要你们的帮助
America Works. But I need your help to do it.

655
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:52,330
你开的价码有点高啊  总统先生
You're putting an awfully big price tag on this, Mr. President.

656
00:37:52,330 --> 00:37:54,900
不  是你们开了高额价码
No, you've put an awfully big price tag on this.

657
00:37:54,900 --> 00:37:57,590
你们要我占18个月的位子
You're asking me to be a placeholder for 18 months

658
00:37:57,590 --> 00:37:59,410
而我想治国
and I intend to govern.

659
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:01,680
如果《美国就业法案》成功了
And if America Works succeeds,

660
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:04,230
那不管16年谁来竞选
then whoever you choose to run in 2016

661
00:38:04,230 --> 00:38:06,920
都会有全党的支持
not only has the backing of a united party,

662
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,780
更会有一笔可贵的遗产
but a formidable legacy.

663
00:38:08,780 --> 00:38:12,460
社会保障呢  社会福利呢
But Social Security? Benefits. Entitlements.

664
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:14,060
我们可不想推选个新人
We don't want to present a fresh face

665
00:38:14,060 --> 00:38:15,620
反过来坑了自己
only to shoot ourselves in the foot.

666
00:38:15,620 --> 00:38:18,300
那就别假装全党统一了
Then let's not pretend to unite the party,

667
00:38:18,300 --> 00:38:21,000
让全党统一支持这项法案吧
let's unite the party behind this legislation.

668
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,630
肯定过不了共和党那关
We'll never get it past the Republicans.

669
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:24,890
我们不是来谈判的
We are not here to negotiate!

670
00:38:24,900 --> 00:38:27,980
你要放眼未来吗  鲍勃  快放眼看啊
You want forward-thinking, Bob? Then think forward.

671
00:38:27,980 --> 00:38:31,610
想16年推举个新人吗  想通力合作吗
You want a fresh face for 2016? You wanna work together?

672
00:38:31,610 --> 00:38:33,850
把我的法案递交给国会吧
Then present my program to Congress.

673
00:38:33,850 --> 00:38:36,080
如果通不过  那也没办法
And if it dies there, so be it.

674
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:40,000
但我们至少他妈该试一下
But I want us to fucking try!

675
00:38:48,570 --> 00:38:51,060
我打算让位了
I am prepared to vacate this chair.

676
00:38:52,030 --> 00:38:53,480
你们也妥协一下
Meet me halfway.

677
00:38:54,390 --> 00:38:55,190
很快
Any moment now,

678
00:38:55,190 --> 00:38:58,580
总统就将在东厅向全国发表直播讲话
the president will be addressing the nation live from the East Room.

679
00:38:58,580 --> 00:39:00,340
关于总统讲话的内容
The White House has remained silent

680
00:39:00,340 --> 00:39:02,380
白宫一直闭口不谈
on the subject of the president's speech,

681
00:39:02,380 --> 00:39:05,660
但国会有消息称  是关于近几个月来
but sources in Congress say it will focus on the jobs initiative

682
00:39:05,660 --> 00:39:08,320
总统一直在筹备的就业法案
he's been planning to unveil for several months.

683
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:10,460
该法案被称作《美国就业法案》
The program, dubbed America Works,

684
00:39:10,470 --> 00:39:12,010
一直在秘密起草中
was developed in secret.

685
00:39:12,010 --> 00:39:14,800
具体细节尚不明了
Any details are the by-product of speculation,

686
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,860
