谢谢
Thank you.

724
00:40:42,610 --> 00:40:45,230
先生  我们五秒后开始
Sir, we're ready for you in five seconds.

725
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:52,080
晚上好
Good evening.

726
00:40:52,530 --> 00:40:56,160
一直以来  我们华盛顿的人都没说实话
For too long, we in Washington have been lying to you.

727
00:40:56,190 --> 00:40:57,940
我们说为人民服务
We say we're here to serve you,

728
00:40:57,940 --> 00:41:00,900
但实际上  我们却自私自利
when in fact, we're serving ourselves.

729
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:05,660
为什么  因为我们只想着连任
And why? We are driven by our own desire to get reelected.

730
00:41:05,660 --> 00:41:10,030
我们渴望继续执政而忽视了治国之职
Our need to stay in power eclipses our duty to govern.

731
00:41:10,390 --> 00:41:12,380
今晚  这到此为止
That ends tonight.

732
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:15,850
今晚  我告诉你们实话
Tonight, I give you the truth.

733
00:41:16,370 --> 00:41:18,120
实话就是  
And the truth is this:

734
00:41:18,810 --> 00:41:21,790
美国梦让你们失望了
The American dream has failed you.

735
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:26,550
努力工作  遵守规则  不保证你们能成功
Work hard? Play by the rules? You aren't guaranteed success.

736
00:41:26,550 --> 00:41:30,070
你们孩子的生活不会比你们好
Your children will not have a better life than you did.

737
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:32,660
一千万美国人非常想
Ten million of you can't even get a job,

738
00:41:32,660 --> 00:41:35,090
找工作却找不到
even though you desperately want one.

739
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:39,960
我们被社保  医保  医疗补助  社会福利
We've been crippled by Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid,

740
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:42,570
所牵绊
by welfare, by entitlements.

741
00:41:42,790 --> 00:41:47,230
这才是问题的根源  福利
And that is the root of the problem: entitlements.

742
00:41:48,140 --> 00:41:52,960
我说明白了  没有天生的福利
Let me be clear. You are entitled to nothing.

743
00:41:54,570 --> 00:41:58,730
没有天生的福利
You are entitled to nothing.

744
00:41:59,530 --> 00:42:02,580
美国的根基是勤劳精神
America was built on the spirit of industry.

745
00:42:02,580 --> 00:42:06,330
未来靠自己努力  而非靠人施予
You build your future. It isn't handed to you.

746
00:42:06,450 --> 00:42:07,840
华盛顿的问题
And the problem with Washington

747
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:10,720
在于没有给你们打造生活的工具
is that we haven't given you the tools to build it.

748
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:12,990
政府为人民服务的唯一办法
The only way for us to serve you

749
00:42:12,990 --> 00:42:16,410
就是想办法让你们服务自己
is to give you the means to serve yourselves.

750
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:19,420
这就是我想要做的
Well, that's exactly what I intend to do.

751
00:42:19,420 --> 00:42:21,880
不施舍  而是给工作
Not handouts. Jobs.

752
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:24,760
实实在在的工作
Real paying jobs.

753
00:42:25,070 --> 00:42:27,560
在未来几周  民主党领导人
In the next few weeks, the Democratic leadership

754
00:42:27,570 --> 00:42:31,360
会提出一个叫《美国就业法案》的项目
will introduce a program called "America Works."

755
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:33,330
其目的很简单
Its goal is simple:

756
00:42:33,330 --> 00:42:37,610
让一千万没有工作的美国人有工作
to put the ten million Americans who are unemployed to work.

757
00:42:37,610 --> 00:42:42,280
每一个想工作的人都会有工作
All of them. If you want a job, you get one.

758
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:45,720
这需要五千亿美元
The cost is five hundred billion dollars.

759
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:47,850
这个数目很庞大
Now, that's a lot of money.

760
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:57,680
{\pos(94.8,216.9)}{\an7}{\pos(94.5,217.35)}安德伍德总统宣布就业计划

761
00:42:47,850 --> 00:42:50,920
为了这笔钱  我们得完全重新思考
To pay for it, we'll need to rethink Social Security,

762
00:42:50,920 --> 00:42:53,920
社保  医保和福利政策
healthcare and benefits from the ground up.

763
00:42:53,930 --> 00:42:58,060
我们不能维持现有的福利政策
We can't maintain the welfare state as we know it.

764
00:42:58,500 --> 00:43:00,730
这么说很不讨人喜欢
Now, that's not a popular thing to say.

765
00:43:00,820 --> 00:43:04,000
任何竞选者都不会说这些话
Anyone running for office wouldn't dare utter those words.

766
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:06,310
每一个幕僚  顾问和下属
Every advisor and consultant and staff member

767
00:43:06,310 --> 00:43:09,840
都不希望总统候选人说这种话
would beg a presidential candidate not to say them.

768
00:43:10,210 --> 00:43:12,050
但我可以说
But I can say them.

769
00:43:12,330 --> 00:43:14,220
因为2016年  
Because I will not be seeking

770
00:43:14,220 --> 00:43:17,420
我将不参与总统竞选
the Democratic nomination in 2016.

771
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:22,390
候选人都谨言慎行
Candidates are cautious.

772
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:25,730
他们含糊其辞  回避周旋  小心翼翼
They must equivocate. They dodge and tiptoe.

773
00:43:25,820 --> 00:43:29,960
但我更愿离开这间办公室时  能完成有价值的事
But I'd rather leave this office having accomplished something of value

774
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:34,220
而不是为了再任四年而无所作为
than secure another four years having done nothing at all.

775
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:38,830
富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福提出新政
Franklin Delano Roosevelt ushered in an era of hope and progress

776
00:43:38,830 --> 00:43:40,960
让美国走向希望和进步的时代
when he proposed the New Deal.

777
00:43:40,970 --> 00:43:44,530
当时  他的改革被认为很激进
And at the time, his reforms were considered radical.

778
00:43:44,580 --> 00:43:49,010
但他说  "这个国家需要进行
But he once said, "This country demands bold,

779
00:43:49,010 --> 00:43:51,270
大胆而执着的实验
persistent experimentation.

780
00:43:51,270 --> 00:43:54,550
想办法  试一试很正常
It is common sense to take a method and try it.

781
00:43:54,550 --> 00:43:58,480
如果失败了  坦白承认  然后重新来过
And if it fails, admit it frankly and try another.

782
00:43:58,490 --> 00:44:01,450
但重要的  是要尝试"
But above all, try something."

783
00:44:01,930 --> 00:44:03,970
罗斯福比谁都明白
Roosevelt would have understood better than anyone

784
00:44:03,970 --> 00:44:07,070
尝试特别办法的必要性
the necessity for trying something different.

785
00:44:07,160 --> 00:44:09,730
新政成功了那么多年
The New Deal succeeded for many years,

786
00:44:09,730 --> 00:44:14,160
但在新政失效前  我们得尝试更新的东西
but we must now try something newer before it fails us.

787
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:16,280
如果《美国就业法案》成功了  
If America Works succeeds,

788
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:19,210
我们将彻底改造美国梦
we will reinvent the American dream.

789
00:44:19,210 --> 00:44:21,250
如果我们的尝试失败
If we fail in our attempt,

790
00:44:21,250 --> 00:44:24,170
我们会坦白承认  然后重新来过
we will admit it frankly and try another.

791
00:44:24,170 --> 00:44:28,820
但重要的  是要尝试
But above all, we must try something.

792
00:44:29,600 --> 00:44:33,470
谢谢  天佑美利坚合众国
Thank you, and God Bless the United States of America.

793
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:51,440
现在是凌晨2点
It's two in the morning.

794
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:53,890
是啊  我刚离开白宫
Yeah, I just left the White House.

795
00:44:53,890 --> 00:44:55,600
新闻发布会  电话  邮件
The press conference, phone calls, emails,

796
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:57,310
其它的明天再说
the rest can wait until tomorrow.

797
00:44:57,570 --> 00:45:00,320
-你睡了吗  -还没
- Were you asleep? - No.

798
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:02,860
这地方不错
This is a cool place.

799
00:45:04,240 --> 00:45:05,450
租金多少
How much is your rent?

800
00:45:07,760 --> 00:45:09,650
你不是说《美就法》暂停了吗
I thought you said AmWorks was on hold.

801
00:45:09,680 --> 00:45:11,640
当时确实是  现在不是了
Well, it was and then it wasn't.

802
00:45:12,380 --> 00:45:14,040
领导层不想让他参选
The leadership didn't want him to run.

803
00:45:14,940 --> 00:45:15,680
谁告诉你的
Who told you that?

804
00:45:15,680 --> 00:45:19,360
没人  但我猜这是他那番讲话的唯一理由
Nobody. But I figure it's the only reason he'd make that speech.

805
00:45:20,370 --> 00:45:23,450
-但他仍会参加竞选吧  -他说不会
- He's still gonna run though, isn't he? - He says he's not.

806
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:25,780
我永远都比你更了解他  赛斯
I know him better than you ever will, Seth.

807
00:45:26,330 --> 00:45:27,910
他不可能不参选
There's no way he doesn't run.

808
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:33,390
这是你来的原因吗  因为他需要我帮他
Is that why you're here? Because he needs my help now?

809
00:45:34,410 --> 00:45:37,640
不  我就是想亲自来看看你的状况
No, I just-- I wanted to check up with you in person this time.

810
00:45:39,940 --> 00:45:42,890
-是他要你来的  -是
- He asked you to. - Yes.

811
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:46,620
不过我把你的邮件发给他了
I did send him your email, though.

812
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:49,840
-他说什么  -我不确定他看过没
- What did he say? - I'm not sure if he's read it.

813
00:45:57,480 --> 00:45:58,970
你是不是该睡觉了
You should probably get some sleep, huh?

814
00:46:00,830 --> 00:46:02,550
明天可是新闻团队的大日子
Big day for the press team tomorrow.

815
00:46:07,510 --> 00:46:09,310
你可以回禀说我活得好好的
You can report back. Alive and well.

816
00:46:11,200 --> 00:46:13,540
我时不时来看你一眼可以吗
Is it okay if I stop by now and then?

817
00:46:13,540 --> 00:46:14,750
我有的选吗
Do I have a choice?

818
00:46:15,570 --> 00:46:18,400
我没有  但是我又不能逼你开门
I don't, but I can't force you to open the door.

819
00:46:20,460 --> 00:46:21,380
随便你了
Whatever you want.

820
00:46:22,870 --> 00:46:23,740
多谢
Thanks.

821
00:46:25,190 --> 00:46:26,240
再见
I'll see you soon.

822
00:47:20,410 --> 00:47:21,310
邓巴女士
Ms. Dunbar.

823
00:47:21,320 --> 00:47:22,540
总统先生
Mr. President.

824
00:47:23,410 --> 00:47:25,730
上次我们谈话时我心事重重
I had a lot on my mind when we last spoke.

825
00:47:25,740 --> 00:47:28,210
-昨晚的演讲  -是一个重大决定
- The speech last night, it was-- - Yes, it was a big decision

826
00:47:28,210 --> 00:47:30,320
如果我之前显得心不在焉  我很抱歉
and I apologize if I was distracted.

827
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:33,370
-没事的  -来谈谈无人机袭击案
- Not at all, sir. - So, the drone strike case.

828
00:47:33,370 --> 00:47:35,690
你一直在走国家机密的抗辩策略
You've been pursuing the State secrets defense.

829
00:47:35,690 --> 00:47:36,680
是的  先生
Yes, sir.

830
00:47:38,470 --> 00:47:41,120
-希瑟  我能这样称呼你吗  -请便
- Heather-- May I call you Heather? - Please.

831
00:47:42,130 --> 00:47:43,980
美国人民反感秘密
The American people are sick of secrets.

832
00:47:43,980 --> 00:47:46,490
这就是我昨晚竭力想说明的
That's the point I was trying to make last night.

833
00:47:46,630 --> 00:47:49,570
我承诺给大家真相  现在就要履行诺言
I promised the truth, and now we're going to deliver.

834
00:47:49,570 --> 00:47:51,560
是什么真相  先生
What truth is that, sir?

835
00:47:51,560 --> 00:47:54,140
一名美国公民被炸断了腿
A man had his legs blown off. An American citizen.

836
00:47:54,140 --> 00:47:55,450
我们要承认
We're going to own up to that.

837
00:47:55,450 --> 00:47:58,380
承认是中情局实施了那次无人机袭击
We're going to admit that the CIA conducted the drone strike

838
00:47:58,380 --> 00:48:01,570
-并且解释原因  -这些信息是机密
- and explain the reasons why. - That information is classified.

839
00:48:01,570 --> 00:48:02,720
不再是了
Not anymore.

840
00:48:02,720 --> 00:48:05,920
我准许你  公开机密
You have my permission to make the classified brief public.

841
00:48:06,980 --> 00:48:09,830
先生  这么做在法律上不合理
Sir, that is not a sound legal approach.

842
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:10,890
但这正是这个国家所需要的
But it's what the country needs.

843
00:48:10,890 --> 00:48:12,020
我们不是在向国家抗辩
We're not appealing to the country.

844
00:48:12,030 --> 00:48:14,210
-而是九个大法官  -错
- We're appealing to nine justices. - Wrong.

845
00:48:14,210 --> 00:48:17,700
我们要承担责任  一石二鸟地博得好感
We're appealing to both by taking responsibility.

846
00:48:17,760 --> 00:48:20,890
是  有人被炸残  他家人被杀
Yes, a man was maimed, his family members were killed.

847
00:48:20,890 --> 00:48:24,600
但因此  成百上千的生命得以获救
But hundreds, perhaps thousands of lives were saved as a result.

848
00:48:24,600 --> 00:48:26,650
我明白这种情感逻辑
I understand the emotional logic,

849
00:48:26,650 --> 00:48:28,640
-但我们不能...  -你坐在那儿对我说
- but we can't-- - You sat right there and told me

850
00:48:28,640 --> 00:48:32,280
-就连最高法院法官也会心软  -对  但
- even Supreme Court justices have hearts. - Yes, but--

851
00:48:32,280 --> 00:48:34,750
我不能告诉你怎么做好你的工作
Far be it from me to tell you how to do your job.

852
00:48:34,750 --> 00:48:36,560
我这一生中  从未做过律师
I've never practiced law a day in my life.

853
00:48:36,560 --> 00:48:38,650
但我书写法律
But I have written them.

854
00:48:38,900 --> 00:48:42,960
我占着这间办公室  我知道国家需要什么
And occupying this office, I know what the country needs.

855
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:44,610
它需要了结
It needs closure.

856
00:48:47,920 --> 00:48:49,530
我去写新的抗辩了
Let me work on a new argument.

857
00:48:50,290 --> 00:48:52,660
-谢谢  希瑟  -谢谢  总统先生
- Thank you, Heather. - Thank you, Mr. President.

858
00:49:00,150 --> 00:49:01,660
总统夫人  您想把它们放在哪
Where do you want these, ma'am?

859
00:49:01,830 --> 00:49:03,290
只要不是这里  哪都行
Anywhere. Just not in here.

860
00:49:03,290 --> 00:49:04,200
好
Okay.

861
00:49:06,670 --> 00:49:08,380
-斯科特 -怎么了
- Scott? - Yes?

862
00:49:09,050 --> 00:49:10,180
这儿还有一些
Here's a couple more.

863
00:49:19,470 --> 00:49:22,910
*让城镇从你身边漂过*
*Let the towns drift slowly by

864
00:49:23,490 --> 00:49:26,600
*听铁路车轮哼鸣*
*Listen to the steel rails hummin'*

865
00:49:27,090 --> 00:49:29,810
*这就是流浪者的催眠曲*
*That's a hobo's lullaby*

866
00:49:31,270 --> 00:49:33,970
*别为明天担忧*
*Do not think about tomorrow*

867
00:49:34,930 --> 00:49:37,610
*让明天来  任明天去*
*Let tomorrow come and go*

868
00:49:38,310 --> 00:49:40,810
*今晚你睡在温暖的车厢*
*Tonight you've got a nice warm boxcar*

869
00:49:41,770 --> 00:49:43,590
想不想来份花生酱果冻三明治
You want a peanut butter and jelly?

870
00:49:44,450 --> 00:49:45,500
不了  谢谢
No, thanks.

871
00:49:52,190 --> 00:49:53,630
一切都还好吗
Is everything all right?

872
00:49:58,270 --> 00:50:00,500
我想做联合国大使  弗兰西斯
I want the UN job, Francis.

873
00:50:01,340 --> 00:50:02,540
参议院两周后就休会了
The Senate goes home in two weeks.

874
00:50:02,540 --> 00:50:04,610
我要你进行休会任命
I want a recess appointment.

875
00:50:05,450 --> 00:50:07,320
我为此做了准备  我能胜任
I prepared for it. I can do this.

876
00:50:07,320 --> 00:50:08,380
等一切结束后
And after it's all over,

877
00:50:08,380 --> 00:50:10,350
如果我成功胜任我知道我能胜任的工作
if I've done the job I know I can do,

878
00:50:10,350 --> 00:50:12,840
我今后做什么都行了
I'll be positioned for anything I want.

879
00:50:13,420 --> 00:50:13,850
克莱尔
Claire--

880
00:50:13,850 --> 00:50:15,430
我和白宫法律顾问确认过了
Now, I checked with the White House Counsel.

881
00:50:15,430 --> 00:50:17,610
在提名被否决后
There is precedent for a recess appointment

882
00:50:17,610 --> 00:50:18,850
有休会任命的先例
after a rejected nomination.

883
00:50:18,850 --> 00:50:20,810
只有一次  但你肯定不是首例
Only once, but you wouldn't be the first.

884
00:50:20,810 --> 00:50:23,240
我知道你在政治上会遭非议
And I know you'll take a hit politically.

885
00:50:23,240 --> 00:50:25,380
我也清楚人们会认为我不配
And I know people will think I don't deserve it.

886
00:50:25,380 --> 00:50:26,360
他们对我会心存顾虑
They'll have doubts in me.

887
00:50:26,360 --> 00:50:30,280
可如果我们只能走到这一步了呢
But what if... this is as far as we get?

888
00:50:30,620 --> 00:50:33,140
如果18个月后一切都将结束
What if it's all over in 18 months?

889
00:50:33,770 --> 00:50:37,180
我不想等  也不想屈就
I don't want to wait, or settle for something else,

890
00:50:37,180 --> 00:50:39,860
-尤其是我已经投入了这么多...  -好吧
- when I've put all this work into-- - Okay.

891
00:50:41,660 --> 00:50:42,650
我会做的
I'll do it.

892
00:50:45,740 --> 00:50:48,230
-你确定不来半块  -我不饿
- You sure you don't want half? - I'm not hungry.

893
00:50:48,590 --> 00:50:49,950
如果你找我  我在书房
I'll be in my study.

894
00:52:08,850 --> 00:52:18,850
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}美国第二任总统约翰·亚当斯的夫人阿比盖尔·亚当斯
在美国独立革命时期和建国后夫君担任总统期间
一直以挚友和参谋的身份
在国家事务上给予约翰·亚当斯宝贵的意见和建议
富兰克林·罗斯福总统的第一夫人
埃莉诺·罗斯福一直坚持拥有独立的事业追求
成为第一夫人后还继续作为教师承担教学工作
同时坚持不懈地推动美国社会在人权和妇女权益方面的进步
罗斯福总统过世后  埃莉诺继续为自己的信仰和追求进行着不懈的努力
1945年  她被杜鲁门总统任命为美国首位驻联合国大使
后还成为联合国人权委员会的首任主席
她被认为是美国历史上最伟大的第一夫人

895
00:52:33,850 --> 00:52:43,850
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}希拉里·克林顿是现代美国历史上
第一位在白宫西区拥有自己办公室的第一夫人
比尔·克林顿刚刚当选总统后  便力排众议
破天荒地委任自己的第一夫人来领导医疗改革
希拉里虽满腔热情
但她主导的医疗改革被国会山上的议员们打得片甲不留  惨败收场
但这没有让希拉里放弃自己的政治野心
离开白宫后  她先是成功当选纽约州参议员
继而参加了2008总统大选  虽然最后没有战胜奥巴马
但是虽败犹荣  并受命担任了奥巴马政府的国务卿
在目前美国两党紧锣密鼓地筹备2016总统大选之际
几乎所有人都认同  希拉里不仅是民主党中最有实力的潜在候选人
而且面对共和党对手也有着巨大的优势

896
00:52:58,850 --> 00:53:08,850
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}美国政府部门大部分重要岗位的人事任命  不仅需要总统提名
还需要参议院经过听证会质询后  投票任命才能生效
当总统特别希望提名某人担任某个职位
而此人得不到议员们的认可和支持时
白宫有时候会利用参议院处于休会状态时进行提名
从而避开参议院听证这一步  让提名人直接上任
但这种"休会任命"如果经常发生  不仅会引起国会反弹
也会给选民一种不尊重民主制度的印象
2012年  奥巴马曾通过"休会任命"的手段任命了四名政府官员
但该任命在2014年被美国最高法院判定为违宪

